Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.91,0:02:01.85,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 8\NThe Pocket Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.73,0:02:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.12,0:02:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The latch on the back gate is creaky.\NWant me to oil it later?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.02,0:02:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please do. The mistress would also\Nlike you to shorten her stick by an inch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.63,0:02:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.93,0:02:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has Kelly's temperature dropped?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.40,0:02:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She's recovered from her cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.43,0:02:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, she's had no\Nappetite the last few days...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:03:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose it does take\Nthe elderly a while to recuperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.11,0:03:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sugar, a pound of tea, a pint of vinegar,\Nand a quart of milk should always be stocked."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.02,0:03:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Red lentils, broad beans, and shallots..."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.99,0:03:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...are cheapest at the\Ngreen grocers in Covent Garden."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.73,0:03:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.30,0:03:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to be a wonderful wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.37,0:03:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was asked to give you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.21,0:03:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.75,0:03:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.48,0:04:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You made breakfast?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.01,0:04:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you try to eat a little?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.75,0:04:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really that hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.55,0:04:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you should at least try a mouthful...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.73,0:04:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe just the soup...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.24,0:04:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you receive another letter\Nfrom Young Master Jones?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.52,0:04:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's easy to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.56,0:05:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What beautiful weather!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.60,0:05:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a shame I can't take a walk in\NHyde Park on such a wonderful day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.87,0:05:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once your leg mends,\Nyou can go whenever you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.31,0:05:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.21,0:05:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Al?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.41,0:05:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The latch on the gate is broken,\Nso he's gone to buy a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.69,0:05:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's stopped again...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.23,0:05:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It stops so often these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.30,0:05:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For years, I would wind\Nit 1 5 times every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.71,0:05:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to wind it more these days,\Nsince I haven't been using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.21,0:05:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.18,0:05:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I take it in to be mended, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.76,0:06:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.22,0:06:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.76,0:06:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.23,0:06:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Your mistress has hurt her leg?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.87,0:06:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.70,0:06:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when my father fell into the Thames\Nyears ago, he lived through it, hardy as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.81,0:06:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when he hurt his leg,\Nit wasn't long before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.01,0:06:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to leave this with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.85,0:06:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They would often come here together,\Nwhen her husband was alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.03,0:06:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. My regards to your mistress.\NI hope she gets well soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.23,0:06:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.58,0:07:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will keep trying to convince my father\Nuntil he understands how serious we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.72,0:07:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,PIease, I want you to trust me and wait for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.04,0:07:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master William?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you inform me when my father returns?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.71,0:07:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.15,0:07:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.09,0:07:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's lndia?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.02,0:07:43.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.16,0:07:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Prince Hakim, you think lndian\Nwomen are the most beautiful, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.70,0:07:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.77,0:07:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I used to think they were...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.14,0:07:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...until I came to London,\Nand noticed the error of my ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.37,0:07:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.14,0:08:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prince Hakim...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.14,0:08:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,English women are all so very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.15,0:08:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, Prince Hakim...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.75,0:08:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.72,0:08:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honored. But I'm afraid I'm already spoken for.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.49,0:08:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.66,0:08:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister gets all the attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.96,0:08:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.93,0:08:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.83,0:08:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's lndia?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.83,0:08:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.57,0:08:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.04,0:08:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been sending a lot of letters recently!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.44,0:08:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Letters? To whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.28,0:08:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious? To Eleanor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.08,0:08:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eleanor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are letters for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.19,0:08:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if they aren't for Eleanor, then who?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.92,0:08:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, they're for business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.19,0:08:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.33,0:09:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hakim...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.80,0:09:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.24,0:09:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that? What kind of person is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.91,0:09:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.98,0:09:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come now, have I met her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.55,0:09:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.61,0:09:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she a Duchess? A Countess?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.25,0:09:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing you, she's a Baronet's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.09,0:09:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.93,0:09:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A maid...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.90,0:09:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A maid...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.87,0:09:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she may be a maid now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.74,0:09:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're lying!\NWell, she may be a maid now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.07,0:09:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.14,0:09:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.41,0:09:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.91,0:09:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.11,0:09:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.81,0:09:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable! I didn't think even you\Ncould have so little common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.72,0:09:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am absolutely against her!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.32,0:09:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're being inappropriate.\NEven a child would know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.99,0:09:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.09,0:09:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.63,0:10:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.00,0:10:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Love can be found anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.27,0:10:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the point!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.54,0:10:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You always think with\Nyour heart instead of your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.07,0:10:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have no grasp of the situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.97,0:10:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're hardly one to speak!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.21,0:10:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you thought about\Nour family's reputation?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.01,0:10:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi! Stay out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.35,0:10:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got things to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.62,0:10:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother! We haven't finished talking yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.10,0:10:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll continue after I've spoken to father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.90,0:10:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to tell father?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.51,0:10:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Absolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.91,0:10:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew what your position would be.\NBut I'm telling you this, regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.45,0:10:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.65,0:11:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She isn't like other maids.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.26,0:11:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her character isn't the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.79,0:11:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.93,0:11:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A wife has many important duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.63,0:11:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must organize dinners, balls and tea parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.30,0:11:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has to converse appropriately,\Ndisplay the correct manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.47,0:11:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must be educated,\Nand speak the Queen's English.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.68,0:11:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can a mere maid accomplish all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.61,0:11:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You told me once yourself, father.\NA gentleman is bred, not born.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.52,0:11:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Through its nature and training,\Na horse can become a champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.39,0:11:38.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, a cat cannot become a horse.\NSome things can't be changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.93,0:11:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you insist on going through with this,\Nthen you'll be banishing yourself from your class.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.93,0:11:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have brothers and sisters, Stevens, and\Nover 1 00 servants that you're responsible for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.74,0:11:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's also the history that your\Npredecessors in the family have created.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.31,0:12:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you not considered these things?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.72,0:12:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you prepared to shun your\Nresponsibilities to satisfy your own desires?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.43,0:12:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the kind of man you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.33,0:12:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think that you can\Ngraft a reed to an elm tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.53,0:12:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Elms grow on hills, reeds live by the water.\NThis is the natural order of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.04,0:12:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Freedom and disorder should\Nnot be confused. Don't forget that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.86,0:12:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might feel better if I wipe you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.97,0:12:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd gotten better...\NIt seems I overdid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.27,0:13:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your stick has been adjusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.18,0:13:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.29,0:13:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you seemed so happy up until recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.92,0:13:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Young people do have their ups and downs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones... wrote me to say\Nthat he would talk to his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.70,0:13:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.94,0:13:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He says that he will make his father understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.04,0:13:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... I know that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.01,0:13:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more realistically I think about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.88,0:13:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the more I realize that the divide\Nbetween our classes... is too wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.63,0:13:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't fret. You'll be just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.49,0:14:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master William...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.09,0:14:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.01,0:15:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really going to sleep there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's more convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.65,0:15:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll turn the light out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.73,0:15:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really am getting old...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.20,0:15:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.64,0:15:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.22,0:16:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have an appetite?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.19,0:16:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.09,0:16:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should really try and eat a little bit\Nof what you fancy. Don't skip meals entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.94,0:16:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is the mistress?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.04,0:16:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, nothing to be done about her age...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.24,0:16:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.48,0:17:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.19,0:17:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.09,0:17:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about a bit of fruit?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.72,0:17:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't have an appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.69,0:17:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Al here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.26,0:17:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.40,0:17:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell him to come and see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.63,0:17:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He comes here every day, but he never\Nbothers to climb the stairs to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.97,0:17:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.98,0:17:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... The mistress would like to speak with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.35,0:17:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Al?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.52,0:17:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.49,0:17:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.05,0:17:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... I was just thinking of planting some roses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.76,0:17:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roses?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.06,0:17:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I could order the bushes\Nfrom a friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.20,0:17:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He owes me a few favors.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.97,0:18:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That... would be lovely...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.01,0:18:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We could have afternoon tea\Nwhen the flowers are in bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.05,0:18:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you want to talk to me about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.52,0:18:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.22,0:18:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if I can be of help, but I'm all ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.80,0:18:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.08,0:18:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gentry and a maid.\NThere's no way they could be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't give her false hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.56,0:18:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true... everything is so complicated...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.46,0:19:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Emma is in love with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.80,0:19:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our Emma...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.27,0:19:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's never felt this way before.\NShe may never feel this way again...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.88,0:19:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sympathize with Mr. Jones,\Nbut I want to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.22,0:19:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.75,0:19:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look after her...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.82,0:19:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look after Emma for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.08,0:19:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pocket watch has been mended,\Nso I was asked to deliver it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.95,0:19:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.92,0:19:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the right one?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.23,0:20:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.56,0:20:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good day!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.17,0:20:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get the doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.78,0:20:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.12,0:20:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.34,0:20:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.86,0:21:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.26,0:21:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your pocket watch has been fixed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.57,0:21:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.47,0:24:10.38,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode:\NAlone
